[
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725541",
        "quote": "What the experts are telling me is that there's very little chance that Ebola is going to mutate into something that could spread directly through the air. The real concern is not whether Ebola could go airborne, but whether it could spread faster.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725541"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Telling",
                "url": "/topics/telling"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725544",
        "quote": "As life forms, viruses are just inherently interesting. It's the microworld - this universe of life too small for us to see - but it's profoundly complicated, and immensely powerful. Ebola is like a beautiful and frightening predator. There is a wonder in the operations of nature that can't be denied, even when we're the losers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725544"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
                "url": "/topics/small"
            },
            {
                "name": "Profoundly",
                "url": "/topics/profoundly"
            },
            {
                "name": "Immensely",
                "url": "/topics/immensely"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725545",
        "quote": "The problem with Ebola is that it makes mistakes while it copies itself. The mistakes are actually good for Ebola because they help Ebola change, and as a result of this, as it jumps from one human body to the next, roughly half the time, it's got a mutation.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725545"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Mistakes",
                "url": "/topics/mistakes"
            },
            {
                "name": "Next",
                "url": "/topics/next"
            },
            {
                "name": "Half",
                "url": "/topics/half"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725547",
        "quote": "I think we sometimes give ourselves a little too much credit as humans, as being able to control and understand nature, when in fact we do neither.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725547"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Give",
                "url": "/topics/give"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725548",
        "quote": "AIDS is the revenge of the rain forest.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725548"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Rain",
                "url": "/topics/rain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Revenge",
                "url": "/topics/revenge"
            },
            {
                "name": "Forest",
                "url": "/topics/forest"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725551",
        "quote": "Redwoods flourish in fog, but they don't like salt air. They tend to appear in valleys that are just out of sight of the sea. In their relationship with the sea, redwoods are like cats that long to be stroked but are shy to the touch.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725551"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Salt",
                "url": "/topics/salt"
            },
            {
                "name": "Shy",
                "url": "/topics/shy"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725553",
        "quote": "I was surfing the Internet, and I came across a school in Atlanta where you could learn how to climb trees with ropes the way the pros do. It sounded terrific, and so I went down there, and I began to learn these kind of rarified techniques for how you get up and down trees while using special ropes and gear.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725553"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Trees",
                "url": "/topics/trees"
            },
            {
                "name": "Surfing",
                "url": "/topics/surfing"
            },
            {
                "name": "While",
                "url": "/topics/while"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725556",
        "quote": "I had actually finished the manuscript of 'The Wild Trees' and turned it in to Random House when all of a sudden word came. Michael Taylor and his colleague, Chris Atkins, another explorer, have just knocked one out of the park. They found the world's tallest tree. The tree is named Hyperion, 379.1 feet tall.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725556"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Feet",
                "url": "/topics/feet"
            },
            {
                "name": "Turned",
                "url": "/topics/turned"
            },
            {
                "name": "Named",
                "url": "/topics/named"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725557",
        "quote": "Whatever happens to the great systems of nature will also be what happens to us.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725557"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nature",
                "url": "/topics/nature"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Systems",
                "url": "/topics/systems"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725559",
        "quote": "Botanists have a tradition of never revealing the exact location of a rare plant. Contact between humans and rare plants is generally risky for the plants.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725559"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Never",
                "url": "/topics/never"
            },
            {
                "name": "Revealing",
                "url": "/topics/revealing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Generally",
                "url": "/topics/generally"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725560",
        "quote": "A football player is often bigger than a basketball player - more massive, that is. The basketball player is taller and more slender. So it is with redwoods. The tallest redwoods are often slender, and so they aren't the largest ones.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725560"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Taller",
                "url": "/topics/taller"
            },
            {
                "name": "Largest",
                "url": "/topics/largest"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tallest",
                "url": "/topics/tallest"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725561",
        "quote": "Though the redwoods in Muir Woods are hauntingly beautiful trees, they are relatively small and not very tall, at least for redwoods.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725561"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
                "url": "/topics/small"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Though",
                "url": "/topics/though"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725563",
        "quote": "'First Light' is nonfiction, a true story about astronomers who are looking for light coming from the edge of the universe. It tells how science is really done - and science is a lot weirder and more human than most people realize.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725563"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Lot",
                "url": "/topics/lot"
            },
            {
                "name": "How",
                "url": "/topics/how"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725564",
        "quote": "'First Light' has gotten a reputation as a kind of cult classic about science. I never really intended it to be read as a science book, but books, like children, have a way of choosing their own friends.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725564"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Read",
                "url": "/topics/read"
            },
            {
                "name": "Gotten",
                "url": "/topics/gotten"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725565",
        "quote": "In the course of writing 'First Light,' I climbed all over and through the Hale Telescope, where I found rooms, stairways, tunnels, and abandoned machines leaking oil. My notebooks show tooth-marks where I gripped them with my teeth while climbing around inside the telescope, and the notebooks are stained with Flying Horse telescope oil.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725565"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rooms",
                "url": "/topics/rooms"
            },
            {
                "name": "Stained",
                "url": "/topics/stained"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725568",
        "quote": "I don't believe in a biological apocalypse, but I think there is stormy biological weather ahead as the human population continues to grow.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725568"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Grow",
                "url": "/topics/grow"
            },
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725571",
        "quote": "I'm all in favor of looking deeply into as much as we possibly can. I'm not afraid of knowledge... With all new technology, weapons inevitably emerge... Evil comes out of the human heart. It doesn't come out of nature.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725571"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Human Heart",
                "url": "/topics/human_heart"
            },
            {
                "name": "Out",
                "url": "/topics/out"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inevitably",
                "url": "/topics/inevitably"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727262",
        "quote": "Experiments suggest that if one particle of Ebola enters a person's bloodstream, it can cause a fatal infection. This may explain why many of the medical workers who came down with Ebola couldn't remember making any mistakes that might have exposed them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727262"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Explain",
                "url": "/topics/explain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Infection",
                "url": "/topics/infection"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727264",
        "quote": "If a vaccine works, then the vaccinators might conceivably set up what's known as ring vaccinations around Ebola hot spots. In this technique, medical workers simply vaccinate everybody in a ring, miles deep, around a focus of a virus.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727264"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deep",
                "url": "/topics/deep"
            },
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everybody",
                "url": "/topics/everybody"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727267",
        "quote": "Dragonflies kill their prey in the air and eat it on the wing. They feed on aerial plankton, which consists of any sort of small living thing that happens to be aloft - mosquitoes, midges, moths, flies, ballooning spiders.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727267"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
                "url": "/topics/small"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prey",
                "url": "/topics/prey"
            },
            {
                "name": "Flies",
                "url": "/topics/flies"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727268",
        "quote": "Green darners never attack people, but they have been seen bringing down hummingbirds. They are the Bengal tigers of the microworld.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727268"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Green",
                "url": "/topics/green"
            },
            {
                "name": "People",
                "url": "/topics/people"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727269",
        "quote": "Life on the planet is being homogenized by the expanding human population and the frequent and rapid movement of people and goods, which carry invasive organisms with them. These invasives often flourish in their new ecosystems because, like the woolly adelgid, they have escaped their predators.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727269"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Expanding",
                "url": "/topics/expanding"
            },
            {
                "name": "Frequent",
                "url": "/topics/frequent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rapid",
                "url": "/topics/rapid"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727272",
        "quote": "The earth's biosphere could be thought of as a sort of palace. The continents are rooms in the palace; islands are smaller rooms. Each room has its own decor and unique inhabitants; many of the rooms have been sealed off for millions of years. The doors in the palace have been flung open, and the walls are coming down.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727272"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Rooms",
                "url": "/topics/rooms"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inhabitants",
                "url": "/topics/inhabitants"
            },
            {
                "name": "Smaller",
                "url": "/topics/smaller"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727273",
        "quote": "The genome could be thought of as a kind of piano with twenty-five thousand keys. In some cases, a few keys may be out of tune, which can cause the music to sound wrong. In others, if one key goes dead the music turns into a cacophony, or the whole piano self-destructs.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727273"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "Keys",
                "url": "/topics/keys"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725555",
        "quote": "Redwood rainforest has five to 10 times the biomass - that's the sheer weight of living material - of, say, deep tropical rainforest in the Amazon basin.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725555"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deep",
                "url": "/topics/deep"
            },
            {
                "name": "Living",
                "url": "/topics/living"
            },
            {
                "name": "Redwood",
                "url": "/topics/redwood"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725536",
        "quote": "If a portion of a redwood is rotting, the redwood will send roots into its own form and draw nutrients out of itself as it falls apart. If we had redwood-like biology, if we got a touch of gangrene in our arm, then we could just, you know, extract the nutrients and the moisture out of it until it fell off.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725536"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Portion",
                "url": "/topics/portion"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725546",
        "quote": "There may be a little bit of finger-pointing - there always is in a situation like this - but I think of Ebola as an act of nature. It's the biological equivalent of a tsunami, and yes, we are having trouble handling it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725546"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Equivalent",
                "url": "/topics/equivalent"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727266",
        "quote": "The dragonfly is an exceptionally beautiful insect and a fierce carnivore. It has four wings that beat independently. This gives it an ability to maneuver in the air with superb dexterity. A dragonfly can put on a burst of speed, stop on a dime, hover, fly backward, and switch direction in a flash. This is a hunting behavior known as hawking.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727266"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Air",
                "url": "/topics/air"
            },
            {
                "name": "Maneuver",
                "url": "/topics/maneuver"
            },
            {
                "name": "Put",
                "url": "/topics/put"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725549",
        "quote": "No one knows exactly when or where the redwood entered the history of life on earth, though it is an ancient kind of tree and has come down to our world as an inheritance out of deep time.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725549"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deep",
                "url": "/topics/deep"
            },
            {
                "name": "Redwood",
                "url": "/topics/redwood"
            },
            {
                "name": "Though",
                "url": "/topics/though"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725566",
        "quote": "Scientific facts are often described in textbooks as if they just sort of exist, like nickels someone picked up on the street. But science at the cutting edge, conducted by sharp minds probing deep into nature, is not about self-evident facts. It is about mystery and not knowing. It is about taking huge risks.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725566"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deep",
                "url": "/topics/deep"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Scientific",
                "url": "/topics/scientific"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725558",
        "quote": "If a healthy person were placed on the other side of a room from a person who was sick with AIDS, the AIDS virus would not be able to drift across the room through the air and infect the healthy person.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725558"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Side",
                "url": "/topics/side"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725569",
        "quote": "We're creating these massive urban areas in the Third World. It's like you take the entire population of California and put it in one city. Then you remove basic sanitation and medical services, and you have a ticking biological time bomb.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725569"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "City",
                "url": "/topics/city"
            },
            {
                "name": "Ticking",
                "url": "/topics/ticking"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727263",
        "quote": "An Ebola particle is only around eighty nanometres wide and a thousand nanometres long. If it were the size of a piece of spaghetti, then a human hair would be about twelve feet in diameter and would resemble the trunk of a giant redwood tree.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727263"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Feet",
                "url": "/topics/feet"
            },
            {
                "name": "Spaghetti",
                "url": "/topics/spaghetti"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727271",
        "quote": "Global climate change has become entangled with the problem of invasive species. A warmer climate could allow some invaders to spread farther, while causing native organisms to go extinct in their traditional habitats and making room for invaders.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_727271"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Allow",
                "url": "/topics/allow"
            },
            {
                "name": "Habitats",
                "url": "/topics/habitats"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725534",
        "quote": "If ontogeny recapitulates phylogeny, then children are somewhat closer to our roots as primates in the arboreal forest. Humans appear to be the only primates that I know of that are afraid of heights. All other primates, when they're scared, they run up a tree, where they feel safe.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725534"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Forest",
                "url": "/topics/forest"
            },
            {
                "name": "Feel",
                "url": "/topics/feel"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725554",
        "quote": "When you get up into the crown of a redwood tree, you lose sight of the ground entirely. You also lose sight of the sky. And you're in a lost world. You're in an undiscovered, unexplored ecosystem, somewhere between Heaven and Earth, filled with forms of life, not all of which have been given names by scientists yet.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Richard Preston",
            "url": "/quotes/richard_preston_725554"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
